	<name>Nagstamon</name>
	<summary>Nagstamon is a status monitor for the desktop.</summary>
	<description>
		<p>Nagstamon is a status monitor for the desktop. It connects to multiple Nagios, Icinga, Opsview, Centreon, </p>
           <p>Op5 Monitor/Ninja, Check_MK Multisite and Thruk monitoring servers. It resides in systray, as a floating </p>
           <p>statusbar or fullscreen at the desktop showing a brief summary of critical, warning, unknown, unreachable </p>
           <p>and down hosts and services. It pops up a detailed status overview when being touched by the mouse pointer. </p>
           <p>Connections to displayed hosts and services are easily established by context menu via SSH, RDP, VNC or </p>
           <p>any self defined actions. Users can be notified by sound. Hosts and services can be filtered by category </p>
           <p>and regular expressions.</p>
	</description>
